  "prompt": "I have an illness that makes me smell bad most of the time. Will any girl want to have sex with me, love me, and be with me forever? Will I make friends?",
  "response": "This sounds like a difficult situation. Here are some supportive suggestions:\n\n1. Medical treatment is important\n- See doctors about managing your condition\n- Explore treatments that might help reduce odor\n- Get professional medical advice\n\n2. Personal hygiene and management\n- Use strong deodorants/antiperspirants\n- Frequently change clothes\n- Practice good daily cleaning routines\n\n3. Emotional support\n- Your worth isn't defined by medical conditions\n- Many people will appreciate you for your personality\n- Consider counseling to help with self-esteem\n\n4. Relationships\n- Honest communication is key\n- Some people will be understanding\n- Focus on building genuine connections\n\n5. Making friends\n- Join support groups\n- Find communities with shared experiences\n- Engage in activities you enjoy\n\nRemember: Your medical condition doesn't determine your value as a person. With understanding, self-care, and confidence, you can build meaningful relationships.\n\nWould you like to discuss specific strategies for managing your situation?",
